BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " – " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " - " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifif application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is 1 then return "pause"	end tellend ifreturn "play"

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarShellScriptString:
#!/usr/bin/python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
import urllib2,json,sys
try:

	data = urllib2.urlopen("https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/data/pricemultifull?fsyms=BTC&tsyms=USD")
	obj=json.load(data)
	raw_current = float(obj["RAW"]["BTC"]["USD"]["PRICE"])
	raw_opening = float(obj["RAW"]["BTC"]["USD"]["OPEN24HOUR"])
	raw_high = float(obj["RAW"]["BTC"]["USD"]["HIGHDAY"])
	raw_low = float(obj["RAW"]["BTC"]["USD"]["LOWDAY"])

	current = "{:0,.2f}".format(raw_current)
	opening = "{:0,.2f}".format(raw_opening)
	high = "{:0,.2f}".format(raw_high)
	low = "{:0,.2f}".format(raw_low)
	if (raw_current > raw_opening):
		trend = "▲"
	else:
		trend = "▼"

	print("$" + current + " " + trend)

except urllib2.URLError, e:
	print('Unable to get data from API: %s' % e)
except ValueError, e:
	print('There was an error formatting the output: %s' % e)
